          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Thankfully, the owner, Travis, has good taste and a healthy respect for the Pantera’s legacy. He’s not looking to subvert your expectations or kill your hero car just to get some likes on Instagram. Instead, the guy dropped $175,000 on a widebody GT4 kit for the DeTomaso and the result is nothing short of fantastic.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2021/03/DeTomaso-Pantera-Wears-A-Widebody-Kit-4.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080,
        "caption": "image credit: YouTube"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Back in the 90s the previous owner of this car had it taken to Hall Pantera, where they put the GT4 widebody kit on it. Many of the classic Panteras have been modified in different ways, both cosmetically and mechanically, so this isn’t considered too uncommon. Still, this particular car looks great.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2021/03/DeTomaso-Pantera-Wears-A-Widebody-Kit-3.jpg",
